---
title: Honey Ginger-Glazed Chicken with Snow Peas and Jasmine Rice
description: We all have a soft spot for the sticky-sweet chicken that’s a staple of takeout dinners and mall food court meals. But it’s not exactly something you would chow down on any night of the week—until now. We’re swapping out the heavy glaze for a fresh burst of ginger and a swirl of honey and soy sauce. Served with tender snow peas on a bed of jasmine rice, this recipe will give you good reason to toss the phone number for your local delivery joint.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/honey-ginger-glazed-chicken-d625c6e3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/honey-ginger-glazed-chicken-3151b061.pdf
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 545 kcal
  fat: 10 g
  saturated fat: 1.5 g
  carbohydrates: 63 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 567 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-ginger-glazed-chicken-5835b3747d69bf090873caf2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring 2 cups water and a pinch of @salt{} to a boil in a
small #pot{}. Once boiling, add @jasmine rice{1%cup}, cover, and reduce to a
simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered.

Trim @snow peas{8%ounce}. Cut @lime{1} into wedges. Peel and mince
@ginger{1%thumb} until you have 2 TBSP. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Season @chicken tenders{24%ounce} all over with salt and @pepper{}. Heat a
large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add chicken in a single layer. Cook until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}
per side. Remove from pan and set aside.

In same pan, heat a large drizzle of oil over medium-low heat. Add ginger and
garlic and toss until soft and fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Pour in
@white wine vinegar{3%tablespoon} and let reduce until almost dry.

Stir in @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, ¼ cup water, @chicken stock concentrate{2},
and @honey{3%jar}. Let simmer until mixture thickens to a glaze-like
consistency, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> The original recipe mentions "we sent more" for the white wine vinegar and honey - 3 tbsp vinegar and 2 tbsp honey are needed here.

Add chicken and snow peas to pan. Toss to coat in glaze. Cook until chicken is
no longer pink in center and snow peas are tender, about ~{3%minutes}. Season
with salt, pepper, and a squeeze of lime.

Divide rice between plates. Top with chicken and snow peas. Serve with lime
wedges on the side for squeezing over.